{
  "flow": "Initiate Import Letter of Credit",
  "product": "ILC-INL (Inland Sight) / ILC-INU (Inland Usance)",
  "source": "Curated from pages/trade-finance/ImportLcFlowPage.ts + data/lcTestData.ts — locators verified against live OBDX 25.1 HBL DOM; merged with rescrape captures from data/scraped/initiate-import-lc-locators-rescrape.json (rescrape-2026-05-21)",
  "urlFragments": {
    "create": "initiate-letter-of-credit",
    "review": "review-letter-of-credit",
    "confirmation": "confirm-screen"
  },
  "notes": [
    "OBDX is Oracle JET — `page.fill()` does NOT commit values; the bound model stays empty. Always drive an oj-input-text via focus → native value setter → input/change/keyup → blur (see utils/ojHelper.ts ojFill).",
    "Numeric ID suffixes (e.g. SelectProduct8713118, BeneficiaryName8826275) are session-scoped on some builds. Prefer the [id^=...] / [id*=...] fallback selectors below when refining a scraper.",
    "Dropdowns: oj-select-one components need ojSelectByText or ojSelectWithSearch — clicking the input alone won't open the LOV reliably.",
    "The 'Read Standard Instructions' checkbox and the Documents-tab Next button need a JS click (.evaluate(... cb.click())) — the OJet wrapper swallows Playwright's standard click.",
    "Two pairs of label twins exist on Tab 1: 'Address' and 'Country' appear once for the Applicant section and once for the Beneficiary section — scope with .nth(0) / .nth(1) or section-relative selectors.",
    "Revolving = Yes MUST be set BEFORE selecting the product, because the product LOV is filtered by Revolving state (Usance/Revolving-capable products only appear when Revolving = Yes).",
    "Usance LC reveals two extra mandatory sub-fields: 'Credit Days From' (textbox, defaults to 'Sight') and 42A 'Drawee Swift Code' + its own Verify button (nth(1)). Sight LC does not render these.",
    "Rescrape merge (rescrape-2026-05-21): 28 test.skip-blocker locators appended across Tabs 1-7. Each merged field carries source=\"rescrape-2026-05-21\" + unblocks=[\"TC-...\"] so future readers can trace them. The rescrape source file is in data/scraped/initiate-import-lc-locators-rescrape.json.",
    "OBDX renders the 7 Initiate-LC tabs as <a href=\"#\"> anchor links (NOT role=tab elements). Click them directly by accessible text to bypass Next-button validation. See scripts/scrape-initiate-import-lc.js for the multi-strategy entry pattern that survives draft-state pollution.",
    "Confirmed absent in the AE/corpmaker2 + ILC-INL Sight build: Limits LOV + View Limit Details + Reset (TC-IMPLC-006); Preview Draft Copy button (TC-IMPLC-047); 4-value 40A LOV (\"IRREVOCABLE\",\"IRREVOCABLE TRANSFERABLE\",\"IRREVOCABLE STANDBY\",\"IRREVOC TRANS STANDBY\") — those test.skip cases need entity/entitlement changes, not better selectors.",
    "Sub-panels that exist but only render after explicit \"Add\" clicks (not captured in initial rescrape, need a 2nd scrape pass to capture): Documents checklist (TC-IMPLC-024), Deposit Linkage on Tab 4 (TC-IMPLC-033/034), Refer Codes overlay on Tab 3 (TC-IMPLC-027), Save-as-Template Yes-state sub-fields on Tab 7 (TC-IMPLC-045)."
  ],
  "menu": [
    {
      "step": "Toggle Menu",
      "selector": "button[aria-label*='Toggle' i], .oj-applayout-drawer-toggle"
